## Bibliotecas


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library("ggplot2")
library("gapminder")
library("dplyr")
```
:::


\newpage

## Suavização

(locally estimated scatterplot smoothing/Local Polynomial Regression Fitting)


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
gap_07 <- filter(gapminder, year == 2007)
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}
```
`geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
```
:::

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/suavização-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Fazendo o suavizador mais nervoso


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(span = 0.2)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/nervoso-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Fazendo o suavizador menos nervoso


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(span = 0.9)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/mais-suave-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Removendo intervalos de confiança


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/sem-IC-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Usando IC de 90%


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(level = 0.90)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/IC90-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Usando um modelo linear ao invés do loess


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/linear-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Usando basic splines para melhorar o ajuste


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y ~ splines::bs(x, df = 3))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/splines-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Usando o gam (general addtive models) com regressão spline


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "gam", formula = y ~ s(x))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/gam-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Começando a construir um gráfico do tipo facet com suavizações


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/primeiro-graf-dispersão-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Dividindo por continente


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ continent)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/facet-continente-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Adicionando suavizadores


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ continent) +
  geom_smooth()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/facet-suavizadores-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Colorindo por continente


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp, color = continent)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ continent) +
  geom_smooth()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/facet-suav-cores-1.png){width=864}
:::
:::


\newpage

## Colorindo somente a curva


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(gap_07, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ continent) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = continent))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula05_files/figure-html/facet-suav-cores2-1.png){width=864}
:::
:::
